	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I made the NES operate with a 9V battery for about an hour, strangely enough. I basically clipped the cord off of the NES 9V adapter, and soldered the end to one of those <a href="http://www.radioshack.com/product/index.jsp?productId=2062219" class="postlink">9V battery snap connectors</a>. I hooked that up to a portable TV to play NES in the car. I don't know why every time I've done it it's lasted so long.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


